<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <!-- F047: the pure, total WRITE HALF of the evidence-reuse store. Three deterministic value
       transformations over the existing F030 `ReuseStore` — `serialise` (the byte-stable INVERSE of the F046
       `FreshnessSensing` read-only deserializer, emitting the `fsgg.evidence-reuse-store/v1` document text),
       `retain` (bounded retention: keep the newest `maxEntries`), and `prune` (superseded-world expiry: keep
       the newest entry per freshness world) — plus a `schemaVersion` token and a `defaultRetentionBound`
       constant.

       The cache-eligibility thread (F029-F046) can READ an evidence-reuse store but never WRITE one: F046's
       shared `FreshnessSensing` edge deserializes the store and maps an absent file to `EvidenceReuse.empty`,
       and F030 ships the pure insert `record`, but nothing serialises a `ReuseStore` back to disk and nothing
       bounds its growth or prunes dead entries — so every run reads an empty store and every gate verdict is
       `mustRecompute noPriorEvidence`. This row delivers the pure half so the cache can warm.

       All three operations are PURE and TOTAL (FR-009): no I/O, no clock, no git, no environment, no network;
       defined for every store including empty; never throwing. Every one preserves recompute-by-default
       safety (FR-008): relative to the unmodified store the result yields reuse verdicts identical-or-stricter
       for every candidate — no operation ever turns a `mustRecompute` into a `reusable` (no spurious reuse).
       `serialise` round-trips losslessly through the REAL F046 reader; `retain`/`prune` remove only whole
       entries (never mutate or fabricate). `prune` reuses the F029 `matches` relation VERBATIM (FR-010) — it
       is exactly `record`'s full-match dedup applied across the whole store; no new reuse policy,
       freshness-match rule, or evidence representation is introduced.

       This LAYERS the store write half on top of the pure F030 `EvidenceReuse` core in a SEPARATE project
       (constitution: heavier capabilities layer on top, not into the core; the F042 `CacheEligibilityJson`
       precedent) so the merged F030 surface stays frozen — additive (FR-012, SC-007): zero edits to merged
       F029-F046 cores or their golden baselines, no schema bump (`fsgg.evidence-reuse-store/v1` is consumed,
       never changed). The IMPURE on-disk persistence (atomic temp+rename write wired into `fsgg route`/`fsgg
       ship`, store-path discovery, the writer port) and the production of REAL evidence references (which needs
       gate execution) are explicit LATER host rows — exactly how F042 delivered the pure cache-eligibility.json
       projection before the F044/F046 host wiring.

       It references ONLY FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceReuse (F030
       `ReuseStore`/`RecordedEvidence`/`EvidenceRef`/`record`/`entries`/`decide`); the F029 `FreshnessKey`
       (`FreshnessInputs`/`matches`/`RuleHash`/`ArtifactHash`/`CommandVersion`/`GeneratorVersion`/`Revision`)
       and F014 `Config` (`CheckId`/`DomainId`/`CommandId`/`EnvironmentClass`) types arrive TRANSITIVELY through
       F030. It adds NO new third-party PackageReference — serialisation is the net10.0 shared-framework
       `System.Text.Json` (`Utf8JsonWriter`) the F042 projection / F025 `AuditJson` / kernel `Json.fs` already
       use (FR-011). Compile order is EvidenceReuseStore.fsi -> EvidenceReuseStore.fs: the curated public
       surface, then the pure bodies. The whole surface is pure total functions — no MVU ceremony (Principle
       IV). The dependency direction stays one-way: EvidenceReuseStore -> EvidenceReuse -> FreshnessKey ->
       Config; no FreshnessSensing/CacheEligibility/RouteJson/AuditJson/Enforcement/Ship/Snapshot/Routing/host/
       CLI coupling. -->
  <PropertyGroup>
    <RootNamespace>FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceReuseStore</RootNamespace>
    <Version>0.1.0</Version>
    <!-- New package identity, packable like Config/Routing/Gates/EvidenceReuse/CacheEligibility/
         CacheEligibilityJson. "Pack output unaffected" means EXISTING packages are untouched, not that this
         library is unpackable. -->
    <IsPackable>true</IsPackable>
    <PackageId>FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceReuseStore</PackageId>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <Compile Include="EvidenceReuseStore.fsi" />
    <Compile Include="EvidenceReuseStore.fs" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceReuse/FS.GG.Governance.EvidenceReuse.fsproj" />
  </ItemGroup>


  <ItemGroup>
    <!-- 073: the shared deterministic-emit helper JsonText.writeToString (pure System.Text.Json leaf;
         NOT the kernel — the pure projections must not reference the kernel/host capability). -->
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.JsonText/FS.GG.Governance.JsonText.fsproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
